---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "AI Agents: From Tools to Teammates — Future";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/future">← Back to Future</a>
        <span class="chip chip--topic">AI</span>
      </div>

      <h1>AI Agents: From Tools to Teammates</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Chatbots answer. <b>Agents act</b>: they plan steps, use tools, check results, and come back with work that's actually done.</p>

      <div class="hero-grid">
        <section class="card card--soft">
          <h2 class="hsmall">What you’ll learn</h2>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>What makes an “agent” different from a chat model.</li>
            <li>The real bottleneck: <b>verification</b> and <b>tool reliability</b>.</li>
            <li>Where agents help today (and where they still fail).</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card card--ink">
          <p class="quote">“The hard part isn't thinking — it's making sure the action happened, and happened correctly.”</p>
          <p class="meta">{updated}</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>TL;DR</h2>
      <div class="tldr">
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--a" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Plan + tools + checks</h3>
            <p>Agents break goals into steps, call tools, and validate outcomes — not just text.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--b" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Best for verifiable work</h3>
            <p>Scheduling, triage, data cleanup, code scaffolding — anything with clear success signals.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot dot--c" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Main risk: silent failure</h3>
            <p>If permissions break or reality changes, agents can confidently return the wrong thing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What is an AI agent?</h2>
      <p class="lead">An agent is an AI system that can <b>decide the next action</b> and <b>execute it</b> using tools (browser, calendar, code runner, CRM, databases). The core loop is <b>plan → act → observe → revise</b>.</p>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="hsmall">The agent loop (simple)</h3>
          <ol class="list">
            <li><b>Goal:</b> “Prepare a weekly report.”</li>
            <li><b>Plan:</b> fetch → clean → summarize → draft.</li>
            <li><b>Act:</b> run queries, export, compute metrics.</li>
            <li><b>Verify:</b> totals, anomalies, citations.</li>
            <li><b>Deliver:</b> file + short explanation + receipts.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="hsmall">What changes vs chat</h3>
          <div class="stack">
            <div class="callout"><h4>State</h4><p>Track tasks, intermediate files, and decisions across steps.</p></div>
            <div class="callout"><h4>Tools</h4><p>Do things in the world: create docs, query systems, trigger workflows.</p></div>
            <div class="callout"><h4>Evaluation</h4><p>Need checks: tests, reconciliations, validations, and human review.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Where agents win (today)</h2>
      <p class="lead">The sweet spot is repetitive work with clear outputs and a way to verify them.</p>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="grid3">
          <div class="mini"><h4>Ops</h4><p>Ticket triage, invoice follow-ups, checklists, SOP automation.</p></div>
          <div class="mini"><h4>Knowledge</h4><p>Drafting with citations, summarizing sources, structuring notes.</p></div>
          <div class="mini"><h4>Software</h4><p>Repo maintenance, scaffolding features, tests, linters and fixes.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note">If you can't define <b>what “done” means</b> and <b>how to check it</b>, don't fully automate it.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Where they still break</h2>
      <p class="lead">Agents fail when the world is messy: ambiguous goals, hidden constraints, drifting data, or overconfidence.</p>
      <div class="card"><ul class="list">
        <li><b>Ambiguous goals:</b> “Make it better” with no measurable target.</li>
        <li><b>Hidden constraints:</b> permissions, missing context, unknown policies.</li>
        <li><b>Reality drift:</b> web pages change, APIs rate-limit, data updates mid-run.</li>
        <li><b>Overconfidence:</b> “success” without hard proof.</li>
      </ul></div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Will agents replace jobs?</summary><p>They replace parts of jobs: repetitive steps and first drafts. The value shifts to goal-setting, quality control, and judgment.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What's the killer feature?</summary><p>Trustworthy execution: logs, citations, confirmations, and reversible actions (undo).</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav" aria-label="Next and previous">
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/future">← Back to Future</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future/longevity-biotech">Next: Longevity →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>


  <style>
    .page{ max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 28px 18px 80px; }

    .hero{ margin-bottom: 26px; }
    .hero-top{ display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .back{ color: rgba(11,11,15,0.70); text-decoration:none; font-weight: 750; font-size: 13px; }
    .back:hover{ text-decoration: underline; }

    h1{ margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 44px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.04em; }
    .subtitle{ margin: 0 0 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); max-width: 72ch; }

    .hero-grid{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.7fr; gap: 14px; margin-top: 10px; }

    .card{ background: rgba(255,255,255,0.90); border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); border-radius: 18px; padding: 16px 18px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
    .card--soft{ background: rgba(245,245,247,0.75); }
    .card--ink{ background: radial-gradient(120% 120% at 20% 10%, rgba(0,122,255,0.18), rgba(11,11,15,0.92)); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.10); }

    .quote{ margin: 0; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 650; }
    .meta{ margin: 12px 0 0; font-size: 12px; opacity: 0.8; }

    .hsmall{ margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 900; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.72); }
    .card--ink .hsmall{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); }

    .list{ margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.70); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 14px; }

    .section{ margin-top: 22px; }
    .section h2{ margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
    .lead{ margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.75; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.66); }
    .note{ margin: 10px 0 0; font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.58); }

    .tldr{ display:flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
    .tldr-item{ display:flex; gap: 12px; padding: 14px 16px; border-radius: 18px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.75); border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
    .tldr-item h3{ margin: 0; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .tldr-item p{ margin: 4px 0 0; font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); }

    .dot{ width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 999px; margin-top: 4px; flex-shrink:0; }
    .dot--a{ background: rgba(0,122,255,0.95); }
    .dot--b{ background: rgba(88,86,214,0.95); }
    .dot--c{ background: rgba(255,45,85,0.92); }

    .two-col{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
    .stack{ display:flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
    .callout{ padding: 12px 14px; border-radius: 16px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.70); border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
    .callout h4{ margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 900; }
    .callout p{ margin: 0; font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); }

    .grid3{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px; }
    .mini{ padding: 12px 14px; border-radius: 16px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.70); border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
    .mini h4{ margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .mini p{ margin: 0; font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); }

    .faq{ display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap: 10px; }
    details{ padding: 12px 14px; border-radius: 16px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.75); border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
    details summary{ cursor: pointer; font-weight: 900; font-size: 14px; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.86); list-style: none; }
    details summary::-webkit-details-marker{ display:none; }
    details p{ margin: 10px 0 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); }

    .footnav{ margin-top: 28px; display:flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
    .btn{ display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding: 10px 12px; border-radius: 999px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.10); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.90); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 800; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.84); text-decoration:none; transition: transform .15s ease, background .15s ease; white-space: nowrap; }
    .btn:hover{ transform: translateY(-1px); background: rgba(255,255,255,1); }
    .btn--ghost{ background: rgba(245,245,247,0.75); }

    .chip{ padding: 7px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.10); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); }
    .chip--topic{ background: rgba(0,122,255,0.14); color: rgba(0,122,255,0.95); border-color: rgba(0,122,255,0.2); }

    @media (max-width: 900px){
      .hero-grid{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .two-col{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .grid3{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 480px){
      h1{ font-size: 34px; }
      .footnav{ flex-direction: column; }
      .btn{ width: 100%; }
    }
  </style>

</Layout>
